  "doc_id": "33409",
  "text": "The LixiLan-L trial [CITATION_1] was a 30-week, double-blind trial, designed to confirm the superiority of IGlarLixi in comparison to glargine alone in patients with T2DM inadequately treated with a stable dose of insulin glargine and any other OAD. The mean starting A1c was 8.5%. Eligible patients entered runin phase where any OAD other than metformin were stopped and patients were prescribed glargine. After 6 weeks, patients were then randomized to IGlarLixi or glargine. Doses were titrated until a fasting glycemia between 80-100 mg/dL was achieved. As in LixiLan-O trial, the maximum glargine dose was capped at 60 IU. The mean results are summarized in Table 2 .",
